CRITICAL POWER SHELL COMMANDS QUICK REFERENCE
powershell
# DISABLE SMBv1 (Critical - Prevents EternalBlue)
Disable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName SMB1Protocol

# DISABLE LLMNR (Prevents Poisoning)
Set-ItemProperty "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows NT\DNSClient" "EnableMulticast" 0

# DISABLE NETBIOS (Security Hardening)
Get-NetAdapter | Set-NetAdapter -NetbiosOptions Disabled

# FIND INACTIVE ACCOUNTS (Security Audit)
Search-ADAccount -AccountInactive -TimeSpan 90.00:00:00

# GET ADMIN USERS REPORT (Security Audit)
Get-ADGroupMember "Domain Admins" | Select-Object Name, SamAccountName

# FORCE GROUP POLICY UPDATE
gpupdate /force

# INSTALL AD DS ROLE
Install-WindowsFeature AD-Domain-Services -IncludeManagementTools

# INSTALL DNS ROLE
Install-WindowsFeature DNS -IncludeManagementTools

# INSTALL IIS
Install-WindowsFeature Web-Server -IncludeManagementTools

# TIME SYNC WITH DOMAIN
w32tm /config /syncfromflags:domhier /update
________________________________________
COMPETITION PRIORITY CHECKLIST ‚ö°
Do these FIRST in timed competition
PHASE 1: IMMEDIATE LOCKDOWN (First 15 mins)
‚Ä¢	PATCH: Install all critical Windows Updates (ms-settings:windowsupdate)
‚Ä¢	FIREWALL: Enable & block inbound by default (wf.msc)
‚Ä¢	DISABLE SMBv1 (PowerShell command above)
PHASE 2: SECURE AUTHENTICATION (Next 30 mins)
‚Ä¢	AUDIT USERS: Delete unknown users (dsa.msc)
‚Ä¢	SET PASSWORD POLICY (gpmc.msc)
‚Ä¢	SET ACCOUNT LOCKOUT (gpmc.msc)
‚Ä¢	DISABLE REVERSIBLE ENCRYPTION (gpmc.msc)
PHASE 3: SECURE SERVICES (Next 15 mins)
‚Ä¢	DISABLE ANONYMOUS FTP (inetmgr)
‚Ä¢	CONFIGURE FILE SHARES
‚Ä¢	DISABLE UNNECESSARY SERVICES (services.msc)

